<h4 style="text-align:center;">Project Day 2: Nacharampeta Thanda</h4>
<p>On the second day of the program, we went to another small village with a population of 500, Nacharampeta Thanda. The night before, we had bought more of the items for the goodie bags and got more bags made locally so that we could put together around 400 more goodie bags, based on the numbers we saw at Natavelli Thanda. The program followed the same format as Natavelli Thanda, with the vaccination site also being set up in the village schoolhouse. The leaders of the village were extremely helpful with their support for my idea and made it a success by informing their villagers of the importance of getting vaccinated both for their village and for their individual families. On this day, I was even told by the nurses and a few of the villagers that I had to have my marriage in this area so they could all come. This talk about hosting my marriage was in the most endearing sense, as marriage is a big part of Indian culture. At Nacharampeta Thanda we were able to vaccinate 100 more people and give them each a goodie bag. The adult population of Nacharampeta Thanda is about 250 people, so we brought the vaccination rate from under 5% to 40%.</p><br>
