<h4 style="text-align:center;">Project Overview</h4>
<p>The week we spent in Kothakota and the six villages we visited to set up the vaccine drives was one of the most rewarding experiences I have had for many reasons. In total, across the 6 locations, we vaccinated just under 500 people who each received an incentive bag of items they needed and could get a lot of use out of. The amount of people my project was able to get vaccinated was truly shocking to me; I initially was not sure if my idea would be a success or make a community-wide difference. The ability, thanks to my parents’ funding, to give each person who got vaccinated a gift bag of things they needed was a small but extremely rewarding aspect of the project; the gratefulness of everyone who received one showed me that even such a small act of service can have a really large impact on someone. In addition, the 6 villages I visited gave me a new perspective on rural living and people living in poverty.  I learned so much about how people in rural areas live, not only in India but also internationally,  and the true lack of resources they  face. I was met with an outpouring of gratitude from the villagers and all the people I met, even though they had to overcome any personal fears they might have had towards a complete foreigner, and I honestly have never felt more welcomed than I did that week. Not only did I feel like I was serving the people from where my mother grew up and where I spent countless weeks throughout my childhood, but they made me feel like I was truly one of them - an international community member. Being able to communicate with the villagers in their native language and bridge the gap between us was such a rewarding experience personally and showed me how important being bilingual is to my identity and just in general, as an international citizen. The gratitude I have for everyone who supported me in my efforts, especially the people I was able to meet in the villages, is immense, and I will always remember and be thankful for this experience. </p><br>
<h4 style="text-align:center;">Future Goals</h4>
<p>I hope to travel back to India in the summer of 2022 and kickstart Goodies Against Covid once again, if the need for vaccinations is prevalent, or even try a similar initiative in a different area of the public health crisis.  </p><br>
