<h4 style="text-align:center;">Thank You's</h4>
<p>This project would not have been successful or even possible without the help of so many people who put great effort into an initiative that was not their own and which they did not know would be successful. I received so much support during my time in India and I will forever be thankful for all those who helped me in all the different areas and nuances of the project. My mom and I, both of us living in America, could only plan so much before we arrived in India and would not have been able to achieve anything once we arrived without the outpouring of support we received. I would especially like to thank my great-uncle, P. Vishsweshwar, for putting his full effort into the planning of this project. With his help, we were able to get in touch with the local leaders (sarpanches) of the villages as well as the PHC, and he was an essential part of the project’s success. His initiatives do not go unnoticed and I am extremely thankful for his help. I would also like to thank my great-aunt P. Sukeshini, the municipal chairperson of Kothakota, for her investment in my project and the ability and resources she provided towards it. I would also like to thank the MLA Sri Ala Venkateshwar Reddy, for helping us to get vaccines onsite and bringing the attention of the local press to the project so that we could expand it. His efforts and his visits to the programming were extremely kind and helpful. Finally, the people who spoke at the programming were key in raising village support for the project and with their help we were able to vaccinate large percentages of the populations. I am extremely grateful to all the following:</p><br>

